"function from the `trpl` crate, which takes a future as an argument and "
"blocks the current thread until this future runs to completion. Behind the "
"scenes, calling `block_on` sets up a runtime using the `tokio` crate that’s "
"used to run the future passed in (the `trpl` crate’s `block_on` behavior is "
"similar to other runtime crates’ `block_on` functions). Once the future "
"completes, `block_on` returns whatever value the future produced."
